<br>
I've been on several dragon raids, but I wouldn't say I'm an experienced raid leader. I've done Vox several times, but never Naggy. I've been in groups killing dragons in WW.<br>
<br>
However, if we get 40 bodies, we can take the dragon down if we follow a simple strategy.<br>
<br>
My guild has many experienced raid leaders, so I can get advice from them.<br>
<br>
A few points off the top of my head:<br>
<br>
1. Resists before AC, get AOE (cold, magic, heat) resists up with buffs or gear.<br>
<br>
2. Melee groups with MA and SA. 2 or three melee groups with clerics and other healers keeping them alive. Melee's goal is not to kill dragon, but get him down to half or less. Stay alive till dragon is at half. Most likely MA and SA will die in this phase.<br>
<br>
3. Nuker groups will pour nukes into dragon when he is at or below half. Nuker groups need healers to keep nukers alive when they are agroed. Most likely lots of nukers will die. Nukers must succeed because melees will be hurting or down. Wait for the Raid leader's signal.<br>
<br>
4. Recovery party. There must be a group of clerics, monks, necros, and paladins for body recovery if things go bad. This group must be on the side lines and listen to the raid leader. He will either say to join in the fight (when it is going well, or a close win that needs an extra boost) or to camp when things are going bad.<br>
<br>
5. Above all !! Raid leader must not draw agro. He or she has to sit safely to call the shots. He must be alive and watching the action to call in nukes. He must determine if the fight is going well or not. He will call the recovery party to camp if things are not going well.<br>
<br>
And a few pointers to combatants. <br>
<br>
1. If it looks like your going to die in combat, stay where you are and die there. Easier to recover your body.<br>
<br>
2. The melee party should consist of a mix of warriors, SK's, monks, paladins, and at least one cleric (bards, rogues, rangers are welcome, too). Paladin's job is to keep cleric alive as well as fight. If melee party is getting wiped, cleric stays with group to keep them alive as long as possible because even the last bit of dmg from a dying group can contribute.  <br>
<br>
3. MA and SA should be either warrior, pally, or SK. It is preferable to let the pally's watch the clerics than be MA or SA. MA is probably going to die, but should have the highest AC, resists, and hps and the ability to hold aggro. I would suggest an SK, cause pally will be busy watching cleric. If SK can keep agro, let the warriors, monks, rangers, rogues, bards, etc deal dmg. You must keep the beast away from the Raid leader, nukers, and recovery party. Keep it in the center of the lair.  <br>
<br>
4. The nuker party needs a healthy mix of casters. The healers should be druids and or shammies, because casters don't have that much hps to heal, and the healers can nuke, too.<br>
<br>
5. Above all, listen to the raid leaders instructions !!\<br>
<br>
<br>
I invite comments from experienced dragon raid leaders.<br>
<br>
It would be nice to have an open raid with enough people 45 - 52. <p>



